<font color="#FF0000">INTRODUCTIONS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 13 13:16:21 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The word is not the thing.  If a word does not denote <br>
clearly an object intended, then it merely connotes.<br>
Tone, then, must be used to convey the emergency of the<br>
situation or the convergence of the emotion and memory.<br>
We think we share a common tool in language...but we don't.<br>
What we share is a common fear of being misunderstood.<br><br>
Take a look at the topic WALTER REED ARMY MEDICAL CENTER.<br>
It is there you begin to find the afterthought, the latter<br>
message of the afterword.  It is there you begin to detect<br>
perhaps the beginnings of entombing the fear of being misunderstood.<br>
Because after-REED, it was finished in every sense of the <br>
word, emotion, or object.<br><br>

